You're missing the `BindingContext`. Your page has no reference to the ViewModel, so the bindings resolve to nothing.

**Fix — set the BindingContext** in your code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Also ensure** your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or inherits `ObservableObject` from the MVVM Toolkit) so the UI updates when properties change:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title = "Hello";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description = "World";
}
```

Alternatively, you can set it in XAML with `x:DataType` for compiled bindings, but the `BindingContext` assignment is still required somewhere (code-behind, DI, or XAML).
